{{Infobox book <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Analyzing Marx: Morality, Power and History | image = Analyzing Marx.jpg | caption = Cover | author = [[Richard W. Miller]] | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[Karl Marx]] | published = 1984 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]] and [[Paperback]]) | pages = 334 | isbn = 978-0691014135 }} '''''Analyzing Marx: Morality, Power and History''''' is a 1984 book about [[Karl Marx]] by the political philosopher [[Richard W. Miller]].
==Reception== The sociologist [[Erik Olin Wright]], Andrew Levine, and the philosopher [[Elliott Sober]] described ''Analyzing Marx'' as a representative work of [[Analytical Marxism]].<ref>[[#Wri92|Wright 1992]]. p. 2.</ref> The philosopher [[Jan Narveson]] wrote that Miller's book is, "an example of the lengths to which a sympathizer must go in attempting to retrieve a theory."<ref>[[#Nar01|Narveson 2001]]. p. 348.</ref>
